🚨 Faltam 4️⃣ dias para começar a janela do #RipCurlWSLFinals!

Lowers left, back when fins were glassed on. Remember nose guards? Anyway, tomorrow at Lowers it looks like there will be a battle for world titles. @ripcurl @wsl finals have been given a yellow light meaning finals will likely run in the next 24 hours!

Taking a break from planes ✈️ for a little while. Terrific year covering @wsl events. 35 flights. 15 events. Here’s how it went: ➡️ San Diego (world Jrs) ➡️ home (pipe and sunset) ➡️ Portugal ➡️ home ➡️ Australia (4 events 2 months) ➡️ home ➡️ El Salvador ➡️ Brazil ➡️ home ➡️ Huntington Beach (US Open) ➡️ Tahiti ➡️ home ➡️ San Clemente (finals)➡️ home ➡️ Malibu (LB champs) ➡️ Brazil ➡️ home ♥️

After wrapping season for @wsl CT, LB and CS tours. I returned home for some rebuilding (literally). I’ve been thru years of knee pain. I’ve tried everything but the grinding of bone on bone made it hard to walk much less surf. So it’s time to rehab and introduce my body to my new knee. I already have hardware in my ankle and plate in my chin so I hope  I don’t set off metal detectors now. Bart and the crew at @fysiohi have been essential in my recovery back to action. Thanks to @surfdochawaii for all the support and always being on call to help. Look forward to getting back to surfing January 2024. Happy Holidays.
